<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 02 at 1:55AM CDT until May 02 at 2:30AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 230 AM CDT
FOR CENTRAL ROBERTS COUNTY...
At 154 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 19 miles northwest
of Codman, or 20 miles northwest of Miami, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
central Roberts County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
